                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77 Chinese Eastern/665: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lay</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-12-11T13:00:00-04:00"
                            >December 11, 1929—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 2 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>172. Referring to Department’s telegram of December 1, 4 p.m., last paragraph.
                    Minister of Foreign Affairs handed me this morning the following statement:
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p rend="center">[Translation]</p>
                        <p>“The Government of Chile, informed of the invitation of the Government of
                            the United States of America to the Governments of China and Russia to
                            consider the stipulations of article 2 of the Treaty for the Outlawry of
                            War in the settlement of their difficulties in Northern Manchuria,
                            expresses to the United States the greatest interest in this pacific
                            action and, as an adherent to the said treaty, hopes that any conflict
                            of that kind may be satisfactorily settled in the spirit of that
                            pact.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>This has also been given to the press and to the Chinese Chargé d’Affaires in
                    Santiago.</p>
                <p>The Minister for Foreign Affairs has decided not to send to China a statement
                    similar to the American one to China as he intended, as reported in my telegram
                    number 170 of December 6, 3 p.m.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lay</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
